git publish [<options>] - Publish last versions of submodules and dev branch of startup module.

    -h|--help               display help
    -q|--quiet              don't print 'Entering ..."
    -t|--vtable             force vtable creation when startup module is a composite submodule
                            (default is to create a vtable when startup module is a bundle)
    -s|--sm-dev             publish dev branches of submodules (default to last version)
    -v|--vtag-only          publish last version of startup module (default to dev branch)
    -u|--reuse              reuse most recent vtag of startup module (move it to current branch tip)
    -j<n>                   number of submodules published in parallel (default to 16)
    --alpha                 publish branch of startup module as alpha version
    --beta                  publish branch of startup module as beta version
    --rc                    publish branch of startup module as RC version
    --rtm                   publish branch of startup module as RTM version (remove pre-release version)
    --dev                   attach to dev branches after publish (default if bundle branch is a dev branch)
    --prod                  attach to prod branches after publish (default if bundle branch is a prod branch)

example:
    git publish             # publish last version of submodules and dev branch of startup module
                            # create a vtable if the startup module is a bundle
    git publish --alpha     # publish last version of submodules and dev branch of startup module as alpha version
    git publish --reuse     # publish last version of submodules and reuse most recent vtag of startup module (move vtag to the tip of the branch)
    git publish -s          # publish dev branch of all modules
    git publish -v          # publish last version of all modules (do not create a vtable)
    git publish -t          # create a vtable when publishing a composite submodule
